{"title":"Boilers and furnaces 20 to 50MW thermal input: process guidance note 1/03","public_updated_at":"2012-05-31T23:00:00Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Regulators can be:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>district councils, borough councils, unitary councils or port health authorities in England and Wales</li>\n  <li>the Scottish Environment Protection Agency in Scotland</li>\n  <li>district councils or the Northern Ireland Environment Agency in Northern Ireland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This <abbr title=\"process guidance note\">PGN</abbr> includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>air emission limits</li>\n  <li>emission monitoring methods</li>\n  <li>best available techniques to control air emissions</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Boilers and furnaces are a ‘Part B’ activity under the local authority pollution prevention and control (LAPPC) regime.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2012-06-01T00:00:00.000+01:00","note":"First published."}],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_2081191\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/611470/process-guidance-note-boilers-and-furnaces-20-50mw-thermal-input.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/611470/thumbnail_process-guidance-note-boilers-and-furnaces-20-50mw-thermal-input.pdf.png\" /></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"attachment-details\">\n    <h2 class=\"title\"><a href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/611470/process-guidance-note-boilers-and-furnaces-20-50mw-thermal-input.pdf\"> Boilers and furnaces 20 to 50MW thermal input: process guidance note 1/03</a></h2>\n    <p class=\"metadata\">\n        <span class=\"type\"><abbr title=\"Portable Document Format\">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class=\"file-size\">256KB</span>, <span class=\"page-length\">34 pages</span>\n    </p>\n\n\n  </div>\n</section>"],"emphasised_organisations":